{% extends "./internal/base.njk" %}

{% block style %}
main img {
  width: 500px;
  float:right;
}
pre {
  display: flow-root;
  overflow-x: auto;
  background-color: rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
  padding: 1rem;
  border-radius: 0.5rem;
}
{% endblock %}

{% block main %}

<h1>Rough Elements</h1>

<img class="logo" src="/img/rough-elements.svg"/>

<p>A robust set of common UI elements with a hand-drawn, sketchy look.</p>

<p>
  The elements are drawn with enough randomness that no two renderings will
  be exactly the same, just like two separate hand-drawn shapes.  They are
  heavily inspired by <a href="https://wiredjs.com/">Wired Elements</a> and
  <a href="https://shoelace.style/">Shoelace</a>.
</p>

<ul>
  <li>Works with all frameworks</li>
  <li>Works with CDNs</li>
  <li>Fully customizable with CSS</li>
  <li>Includes a dark theme</li>
  <li>Open source</li>
</ul>

<h1>Quick Start</h1>
Add the following to your webpage:
<pre>
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@rogerta/rough-element@1/dist/themes/light.css" /&gt;
&lt;script type="module" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@rogerta/rough-element@1/dist/rough-elements.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>
Now use the elements in your page:
<pre>
&lt;re-button&gt;Click here&lt;/re-button&gt;
&lt;re-button variant="text"&gt;
  &lt;re-icon name="arrow-back" slot="prefix"&gt;&lt;/re-icon&gt;Back
&lt;/re-button&gt;

&lt;re-select value="item1"&gt;
  &lt;re-item id="item0"&gt;
    This is a long item for test
  &lt;/re-item&gt;
  &lt;re-item id="item1"&gt;
    &lt;re-icon slot="prefix" name="check"&gt;&lt;/re-icon&gt;
    Item 1
  &lt;/re-item&gt;
  &lt;re-item id="item2" disabled&gt;
    Item 2
    &lt;re-icon slot="suffix" name="close"&gt;&lt;/re-icon&gt;
  &lt;/re-item&gt;
  &lt;re-divider&gt;&lt;/re-divider&gt;
  &lt;re-item id="item3"&gt;Menu item 3&lt;/re-item&gt;
&lt;/re-select&gt;
</pre>

